_children.C: If black has [d16] white can play an asking move to see if [n16] or [o16] is better.  Pass to see this variation. White can tenuki.

This was one of Kitani Minoru 9p innovations during the Shin-Fuseki era.

"The result after [p15] is locally good for White, so this move is not played often." [Kim Sung-rae, 8p - Korean-Style Insei League: 14.11.2010]
